@page "/girlswhoconnect/childsafetystandards"

<PageTitle>Child Safety Standards - Girls Who Connect</PageTitle>

<GirlsWhoWalkHeader />

<div class="gwc-page">

    <section class="gwc-section gwc-hero gwc-hero-compact">
        <div class="gwc-container gwc-hero-grid">
            <div class="gwc-hero-copy">
                <span class="gwc-eyebrow gwc-eyebrow-hero">Legal</span>
                <h1>Child Safety Standards</h1>
                <p>
                    How Girls Who Connect meets the 11 Child Safe Standards through its features,
                    policies, and moderation practices. The app is designed for adults aged 18+.
                </p>
                <p class="gwc-effective-date">Effective 12 August 2025</p>
            </div>
            <div class="gwc-hero-visual">
                <img src="/images/Girls Who Connect/Child.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="gwc-section gwc-section-muted gwc-legal-section" aria-labelledby="policy-title">
        <div class="gwc-container">
            <header class="gwc-section-head">
                <span class="gwc-eyebrow">Legal</span>
                <h2 id="policy-title">Child safety standards</h2>
                <p class="gwc-section-lead">@SectionCount section@(SectionCount == 1 ? "" : "s") covered.</p>
            </header>

            <div class="gwc-policy-blocks">

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="design-choices">
                    <h2>Design choices</h2>
                    <p>
                        Key design choices for safety: The app does not support one-to-one (DM) messaging;
                        conversations occur only in location-based group chats. Users cannot “block”
                        others; instead, moderators review reports and can remove content and accounts.
                        The app uses a rough location (e.g., area/city) chosen by the user to join a
                        location chat; it does not share precise GPS coordinates.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-1">
                    <h2>Standard 1: Culturally safe environment</h2>
                    <p>
                        We promote an inclusive app experience that respects diverse cultural
                        identities, including Aboriginal children and young people. Discrimination,
                        racism, or culturally unsafe behaviour is prohibited and removed upon
                        report/review.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-2">
                    <h2>Standard 2: Leadership, governance and culture</h2>
                    <p>
                        Child safety is embedded in our policies and moderation. We maintain a zero-tolerance
                        stance on grooming, exploitation, or sexualised content involving minors. Any account
                        found to be involved in such behaviour is permanently banned from the app. Credible
                        reports are acted on swiftly, and serious matters are escalated to relevant law
                        enforcement agencies for investigation.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-3">
                    <h2>Standard 3: Empowerment and participation</h2>
                    <p>
                        If a minor is detected or reported on the app, we act immediately to protect their
                        safety by removing their account, securely storing any relevant evidence (such as
                        profile details, chat messages, or images) for investigation purposes, and notifying
                        appropriate law enforcement agencies when warranted - for example, in cases involving
                        suspected grooming, exploitation, or sexualised content.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Currently, concerns can be reported by emailing
                        <a href="mailto:matt@kenyondevlabs.com">matt@kenyondevlabs.com</a>. Additional in-app reporting options are
                        being developed to make it even easier for users to report unsafe behaviour directly.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-4">
                    <h2>Standard 4: Families and communities</h2>
                    <p>
                        We publish our safety rules and procedures on our website so anyone can read them.
                        You don't have to be a registered app user to send us a concern - parents or other
                        community members can email us directly.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-5">
                    <h2>Standard 5: Equity and diverse needs</h2>
                    <p>
                        Safety processes are applied fairly to all users regardless of background or identity.
                        We aim for accessible language and straightforward reporting mechanisms.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-6">
                    <h2>Standard 6: Suitability of people</h2>
                    <p>
                        Admin and developer accounts with moderation powers are vetted before elevated access
                        is granted. Breaches of safety expectations result in immediate removal of access.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-7">
                    <h2>Standard 7: Child-focused complaints process</h2>
                    <p>
                        At present, users can report concerns by emailing
                        <a href="mailto:matt@kenyondevlabs.com">matt@kenyondevlabs.com</a>. In-app reporting features for messages in
                        location-based group chats are being developed to make it easier to flag unsafe
                        behaviour directly. Reports involving suspected minors are prioritised within 24
                        hours, and urgent cases are escalated to law enforcement without delay. We keep
                        reasonable records of all reports and the actions taken in response.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-8">
                    <h2>Standard 8: Knowledge, skills, and training</h2>
                    <p>
                        Admins in the app are users who help run location-based groups. They do not have
                        moderation powers over user accounts or content beyond managing their group activities.
                        All moderation and child safety actions related to the app are handled by the
                        development team.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-9">
                    <h2>Standard 9: Safe online environments</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>No 1:1 messaging; only location-based group chats to reduce private solicitation risk.</li>
                        <li>Rough location only - users select an area or city to join its chat; no GPS sharing.</li>
                        <li>Moderation and reporting: currently via email; in-app reporting for group chat messages coming soon.</li>
                        <li>Developers can remove content or accounts as needed.</li>
                        <li>Explicit or sexualised content involving minors is strictly banned and reported.</li>
                    </ul>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-10">
                    <h2>Standard 10: Review and improvement</h2>
                    <p>
                        We review child safety policies at least annually and after any material incident.
                        We monitor safety metrics (e.g., report volume, response times) to improve processes.
                        In-app reporting features will be implemented soon after rollout to provide users with
                        a faster and more direct way to flag safety concerns.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="standard-11">
                    <h2>Standard 11: Policies and procedures</h2>
                    <p>
                        This page forms part of our public safety documentation. Internal guidelines cover
                        report handling, evidence preservation, account actions, and cooperation with
                        authorities.
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block gwc-policy-block-highlight" id="reporting">
                    <h2>Reporting concerns</h2>
                    <p>
                        If you believe a child or young person may be at risk on the Girls Who Connect app,
                        please report immediately:
                    </p>
                    <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:matt@kenyondevlabs.com">matt@kenyondevlabs.com</a></p>
                </article>

                <article class="gwc-policy-block" id="legal-compliance">
                    <h2>Legal compliance</h2>
                    <p>
                        We comply with relevant UK child protection laws, including the
                        <strong>Children Act 1989 &amp; 2004</strong>, the <strong>Sexual Offences Act 2003</strong>,
                        and the <strong>Protection of Children Act 1978</strong>. We cooperate fully with lawful
                        requests from authorities and report serious offences without delay.
                    </p>
                </article>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer class="gwc-footer">
        <div class="gwc-container gwc-footer-inner">
            <nav aria-label="Legal">
                <h3>Legal</h3>
                <ul class="gwc-footer-links">
                    <li><NavLink href="/GirlsWhoConnect/PrivacyPolicy">Privacy Policy</NavLink></li>
                    <li><NavLink href="/GirlsWhoConnect/ChildSafetyStandards">Child Safety Standards</NavLink></li>
                </ul>
            </nav>
            <p class="gwc-footer-copy">&copy; @DateTime.Now.Year Kenyon Dev Labs</p>
        </div>
    </footer>

</div>

<style>
    :root {
        --gwc-brand: #efb2c4;
        --gwc-brand-dark: #d495a8;
        --gwc-brand-deep: #b14c66;
        --gwc-muted: #fff5f8;
        --gwc-text: #1a1a1a;
        --gwc-text-soft: #4a4a4a;
        --gwc-max: 1080px;
        --gwc-radius: 1rem;
    }

    html, body {
        overflow-x: clip;
        font-family: var(--font-sans, 'Plus Jakarta Sans', system-ui, sans-serif);
    }

    body {
        background: #fff;
        color: var(--gwc-text);
    }

    .gwc-page { overflow-x: clip; }

    .gwc-section {
        width: 100vw;
        margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
        margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);
        padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(239, 178, 196, 0.35);
    }

    .gwc-section-muted { background: var(--gwc-muted); }

    .gwc-container {
        max-width: var(--gwc-max);
        margin: 0 auto;
    }

    .gwc-section-head {
        max-width: 42rem;
        margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
        text-align: center;
    }

    .gwc-section-head h2 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.1rem);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        line-height: 1.15;
    }

        .gwc-section-head h2::after {
            content: "";
            display: block;
            width: 3rem;
            height: 3px;
            margin: 1rem auto 0;
            background: var(--gwc-brand-dark);
            border-radius: 999px;
        }

    .gwc-section-lead {
        margin: 1.15rem 0 0;
        color: var(--gwc-text-soft);
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        line-height: 1.65;
    }

    .gwc-hero {
        border-top: none;
        padding: 3rem 1.5rem 5rem;
        background: linear-gradient(160deg, var(--gwc-brand) 0%, var(--gwc-brand-dark) 100%);
        position: relative;
    }

        .gwc-hero::after {
            content: "";
            position: absolute;
            left: 0; right: 0; bottom: -1px;
            height: 64px;
            background: var(--gwc-muted);
            clip-path: ellipse(55% 100% at 50% 100%);
        }

    .gwc-hero-compact { padding-bottom: 4.5rem; }

    .gwc-hero-grid {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 2.5rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
    }

    .gwc-hero-copy { flex: 1 1 360px; }

    .gwc-eyebrow {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.12em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: #c45f7a;
    }

    .gwc-eyebrow-hero { color: var(--gwc-brand-deep); }

    .gwc-hero-copy h1 {
        margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
        font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.75rem);
        font-weight: 800;
        letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        line-height: 1.1;
    }

    .gwc-hero-copy p {
        margin: 0;
        max-width: 32rem;
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        line-height: 1.65;
        color: var(--gwc-text-soft);
    }

    .gwc-effective-date {
        display: inline-block;
        margin-top: 1.15rem !important;
        padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
        font-size: 0.88rem !important;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--gwc-brand-deep) !important;
    }

    .gwc-hero-visual {
        flex: 1 1 240px;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
    }

        .gwc-hero-visual img {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 200px;
            filter: drop-shadow(0 16px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12));
        }

    .gwc-policy-blocks {
        max-width: 48rem;
        margin: 0 auto;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        gap: 1.15rem;
    }

    .gwc-policy-block {
        padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid rgba(239, 178, 196, 0.4);
        border-radius: var(--gwc-radius);
        box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(212, 149, 168, 0.08);
    }

    .gwc-policy-block-highlight {
        border-color: var(--gwc-brand-dark);
        box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(212, 149, 168, 0.16);
    }

        .gwc-policy-block h2 {
            margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
            font-size: 1.15rem;
            font-weight: 800;
            padding-bottom: 0.65rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(239, 178, 196, 0.35);
        }

        .gwc-policy-block p {
            margin: 0 0 0.85rem;
            color: var(--gwc-text-soft);
            line-height: 1.7;
            font-size: 1rem;
        }

            .gwc-policy-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

        .gwc-policy-block ul {
            margin: 0;
            padding-left: 1.25rem;
            color: var(--gwc-text-soft);
            line-height: 1.65;
        }

        .gwc-policy-block li { margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }

        .gwc-policy-block a {
            color: var(--gwc-brand-deep);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

    .gwc-footer {
        width: 100vw;
        margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
        margin-right: calc(50% - 50vw);
        padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
        background: var(--gwc-muted);
        border-top: 1px solid rgba(239, 178, 196, 0.35);
        text-align: center;
    }

    .gwc-footer-inner h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
        font-weight: 800;
    }

    .gwc-footer-links {
        list-style: none;
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
        padding: 0;
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    }

        .gwc-footer-links a {
            color: var(--gwc-text);
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

            .gwc-footer-links a:hover { color: var(--gwc-brand-deep); }

    .gwc-footer-copy {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--gwc-text-soft);
        font-size: 0.92rem;
    }

    @@media (max-width: 760px) {
        .gwc-section { padding: 3rem 1.25rem; }
        .gwc-hero-grid { flex-direction: column; text-align: center; }
        .gwc-hero-copy p { margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
        .gwc-policy-block { padding: 1.25rem 1.35rem; }
    }
</style>

@code {
    private const int SectionCount = 14;
}
